summary: Ali has had a successful track record of working with senior leadership to drive strategy and achieve measurable results in both private and public companies across different industries. His clients range from large cap public companies that are looking to execute on strategic opportunities, to private firms that need to take their leadership to the next level of maturity to drive profitable growth. Whether he is leading a program implementation or coaching executives, Ali enables leaders to systematically and sustainably articulate and drive their strategic vision in a motivating and developmental way to get the results they seek within their organization while advancing their career goals. His background in neurology and psychology combined with a practical and personable approach to getting things done in business enable him to strategically affect change and communicate with leadership and employees at all levels of an organization.Prior to joining ETW, Ali was President of a multi-million dollar manufacturing and retail operation in Phoenix, Arizona that during his tenure achieved five years of consecutive 25+ percent compounded annual growth. Ali graduated Cum Laude with a bachelor’s degree in the Biological Basis of Human Behavior from the University of Pennsylvania’s College of Arts and Sciences and has successfully completed courses in Economics, Marketing and Finance from the Wharton School of Business.
